{% import "macros/paths" as paths %}
## Analysis

| What | When to use | Path |
|-|-|-|
| Callers (incoming) | Before changing signature or behavior — shows who will break | `Read {{ paths.sym_md("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "CALLERS") }}` |
| Dependencies (outgoing) | Tracing what a function calls — don't Grep for callees | `Read {{ paths.sym_md("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "DEPS") }}` |
| All references | Before renaming, moving, or deleting — every usage site | `Read {{ paths.sym_md("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "REFERENCES") }}` |
| Trait implementations | Working with a trait — all concrete impls | `Read {{ paths.sym_md("file." ~ ext, "MyTrait", "IMPLEMENTATION") }}` |
| Project TODOs | Scanning for outstanding work | `Read @/todo/TODO.md` |

Note: Symlinks in `callers/`, `deps/`, `references/`, `implementation/` are shortcuts to related symbols' `@/` directories — follow to read, edit, and inspect linked symbols directly.
